i18n.pages.accountEdit.openingBalanceHel:
Opening balance is the amount of funds in an account before starting tracking finances.

For example, if you have a bank account with a balance of $1236, enter it here to get correct total balance after registering operations in Journal.

If you have a multi-currency account, you may enter several opening balances per each currency.

The opening balance can be negative for credit accounts.
